\f0\fs54 \cf0 Ginger Scones with Cardamom\

\f1\b\fs32 Yield 
\b0\fs34 Makes 12 scones
\f0\fs42 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural

\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl1
\f1\fs36 \cf0 		3 cups all-purpose flour\
		2 teaspoons baking powder\
		1/2 teaspoon baking soda\
		1/2 teaspoon salt\
		3/4 teaspoon cardamom pods, crushed and inner seeds ground\
		1/2 cup (1 stick) unsalted butter, cut into small pieces\
		1/4 cup crystallized ginger, chopped in 1/4-inch pieces\
		3/4 cup sour cream\
		1/2 cup sugar\
		4 teaspoons sugar\
		2 large eggs\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 		\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural

\f0\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa360\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs36 \cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside.\
{\listtext	2.	}Place the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, the bowl of a food processor, or in a large bowl and mix by hand. Sift ground cardamom seeds into mixture; stir to combine. Add butter and mix until crumbly.\
{\listtext	3.	}Add ginger, sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar, and 1 egg. Mix, blend, or pulse, just until combined; do not overmix.\
{\listtext	4.	}Form 1/3 cup dough into a ball or use a large ice cream scoop, and place dough on prepared baking sheet. Repeat with remaining dough, spacing scones about 2 inches apart.\
{\listtext	5.	}In a small bowl, mix together remaining egg with a dash of water. Brush scones with egg mixture and sprinkle evenly with remaining 4 teaspoons sugar. Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.\
